From ae57e3f443240733759c8ef904368162e43f9c8e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Janos <janos@dot.industries>
Date: Sat, 14 Mar 2026 10:02:47 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: patch __tz.c to load timezone data via virtual
 filesystem

Replace mmap-based timezone file loading with open/read/close to work
with WarpGrid's virtual filesystem shim. This enables localtime(),
strftime(), and other timezone-aware functions to use real TZif v2 data
served by the host through /usr/share/zoneinfo/*.

- Add warpgrid_load_file() using static 8KB buffer instead of mmap
- Re-enable full musl timezone parsing (previously stubbed to UTC-only)
- Export timezone globals (__timezone, __daylight, __tzname, tzset)
- Update expected-symbols for all WASI targets

Part of US-207: Patch timezone loading to use virtual filesystem
